cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with text classification and natural language processing techniques to predict movie genres based on plot summaries.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the paper involves retrieving relevant information from text data to classify movie genres.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper explores several machine learning methods for text classification and multi-label problem involved in genre tagging.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict movie genres.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not involve image analysis, but it may be relevant if the plot summaries were accompanied by movie posters or other visual data.
